HEADWORD: Porotype
<hw>Po"ro*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pore</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, and <er>-type</er>.]</ety> <def>A copy of a print,
writing, etc., made by placing it upon a chemically prepared paper which
is acted upon by a gas which permeates the paper of the print, writing,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porous</ent>⟦br⟧
